context: The Royal Canadian Air Force (RCAF) is headed by <a0_0>the <b4_0>Commander of the Royal Canadian Air Force<b4_0/><a0_0/>. The commander of 1 Canadian Air Division and Canadian NORAD Region, based in <a1_0><b5_0>Winnipeg<b5_0/><a1_0/>, is responsible for the operational command and control of Air Force activities throughout Canada and worldwide. 1 Canadian Air Division operations are carried out through <a2_0><b6_0>eleven<b6_0/><a2_0/> wings located across Canada. The commander of 2 Canadian Air Division is responsible for training and support functions. 2 Canadian Air Division operations are carried out at two wings. Wings represent the grouping of various squadrons, both operational and support, under a single <a3_0><b7_0>tactical commander<b7_0/><a3_0/> reporting to the operational commander and vary in size from several hundred personnel to several thousand.
